$ Excel Object Model: Styles
@ Styles

`styles` is a collection that is managed by a → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Workbook which stores the available → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Style[styles] in this collection.

{ Enumerating styles

  The following simple → development/languages/VBA macro iterates over all styles that are found in a → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Workbook[workbook's] `.styles` collection:
  gh|about-MS-Office-object-model|/Excel/Styles/enumerate.vb||

  In a workbook that has no manually added styles, it prints the predefined styles: 
  table { ll
    20% - Accent1 ☰
    20% - Accent2 ☰
    20% - Accent3 ☰
    20% - Accent4 ☰
    20% - Accent5 ☰
    20% - Accent6 ☰
    40% - Accent1 ☰
    40% - Accent2 ☰
    40% - Accent3 ☰
    40% - Accent4 ☰
    40% - Accent5 ☰
    40% - Accent6 ☰
    60% - Accent1 ☰
    60% - Accent2 ☰
    60% - Accent3 ☰
    60% - Accent4 ☰
    60% - Accent5 ☰
    60% - Accent6 ☰
    Accent1 ☰
    Accent2 ☰
    Accent3 ☰
    Accent4 ☰
    Accent5 ☰
    Accent6 ☰
    Bad ☰
    Calculation ☰
    Check Cell ☰
