    Normal ☰
    Note ☰
    Output ☰
    Percent ☰
    Title ☰
    Total ☰
    Warning Text ☰
  table }

  As soon as a *hyperlink* (using the → Microsoft/Office/Excel/functions/hyperlink[`=hyperlink(…)` worksheet function] or using the → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Hyperlink[`hyperlink` object]) is inserted into the
  workbook, there is also the style *Hyperlink* that allows to customize this hyperlink. When this hyperlink is clicked, the style *Followed Hyperlink* is added.
  -
  See → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Style#xls-style-hyperlink[specifying styles for hyperlinks].
 
}

sa:

  The → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Style[`style` object]

